docs.lead_paragraph: LEAD: Having narrowly escaped financial ruin in the mid-1980's, the Federal Medicare program is now being squeezed as never before, and patients and doctors are both complaining. Some experts say Americans will have to put up more money or expect reductions in coverage, or else the program will become insolvent within the decade.
